Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows markedly elevated serum creatinine, indicating significant renal impairment, and elevated ALT, suggesting possible liver involvement. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low specific gravity and abnormal appearance, supporting renal dysfunction and possible metabolic derangement (e.g., diabetes or dehydration). No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend urgent clinical evaluation for acute or chronic kidney disease and assessment for underlying metabolic or hepatic disorders.
